element.name: Sidetracked - Balbriggan by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: Balbriggan railway station is located on the Dublin-Belfast Railway line

long-description.p: The Dublin & Drogheda railway opened the station at Balbriggan in 1844. The original brick built station building can still be seen today. And typical Great Northern style station masters house, built around 1870.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.
